    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello @aparnakr!\r\n\r\nFixed point math support was [part of our Q2 Roadmap](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/issues/2207), but development [halted](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/designing-fixed-point-math-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2499/26) once the Solidity team recently decided they'd implement it natively, following pretty much the same design patterns we had explored.\r\n\r\nThis was about a month ago, but I don't know if there have been any recent updates. Discussion was happening in https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/409.\r\n\r\nOnce that feature is released, we'll likely want to build some libraries on top of it, perhaps including advanced operations like exponentiation and the like, but that depends on what the Solidity team delivers.",
